WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.042 --> 00:00:03.042
[Ethereal melody;
Soothing. bell-like percussion]

2
00:00:09.792 --> 00:00:12.376
[Delicate violin plucking]

3
00:00:19.251 --> 00:00:22.001
[Sustained. warm violin tone joins]

4
00:00:27.667 --> 00:00:29.959
[Music fades]

5
00:00:59.709 --> 00:01:01.959
[Insects chirp]

6
00:01:04.001 --> 00:01:06.167
[Birdsong]

7
00:01:20.709 --> 00:01:22.834
[Gentle rustling]

8
00:01:28.459 --> 00:01:30.584
[Vehicle approaches]

9
00:01:34.001 --> 00:01:36.042
[Car engine stops]

10
00:01:42.792 --> 00:01:44.501
- [Man] Oh man.
- [Woman] Wow.

11
00:01:45.126 --> 00:01:47.167
[Horse neighs in the distance]

12
00:01:50.584 --> 00:01:53.459
[Man] I haven't been here
since I was a little kid.

13
00:01:53.542 --> 00:01:55.417
[Woman] I thought you grew up here.

14
00:01:55.501 --> 00:01:57.209
[Man] Like round the corner.

15
00:02:00.042 --> 00:02:02.042
I knocked my tooth out on that step.

16
00:02:05.709 --> 00:02:07.251
Got me brain damaged.

17
00:02:07.334 --> 00:02:09.459
[Woman chuckles]

18
00:02:09.542 --> 00:02:11.376
[Man laughs]

19
00:02:12.834 --> 00:02:16.334
[He laughs] It's not New York.
but... it's ours.

20
00:02:17.126 --> 00:02:20.417
- I think it's gonna be pretty sick. no?
- [Door opens]

21
00:02:34.417 --> 00:02:35.626
Yeah?

22
00:02:44.876 --> 00:02:47.876
- I could send for my drum kit?
- [Woman] No way.

23
00:02:47.959 --> 00:02:49.251
[Man] No?

24
00:02:53.167 --> 00:02:55.917
My uncle was a hoarder.
I didn't realise how much...

25
00:02:56.459 --> 00:02:58.209
space there was in here.

26
00:02:58.292 --> 00:03:00.012
- It's peaceful.
- [He climbs up the stairs]

27
00:03:00.084 --> 00:03:02.751
I can just record
an album out here so easily.

28
00:03:05.084 --> 00:03:07.251
- Gracie!
- What?

29
00:03:07.334 --> 00:03:08.542
[Man] I found an office!

30
00:03:09.792 --> 00:03:11.626
[Grace] Oh.

31
00:03:11.709 --> 00:03:14.501
[Man] You can write
your Great American Novel up here.

32
00:03:14.584 --> 00:03:16.251
Whoa!

33
00:03:16.334 --> 00:03:18.042
What?

34
00:03:18.126 --> 00:03:19.542
[Man] Um...

35
00:03:20.167 --> 00:03:23.001
It's alright.
It's just a little rat situation.

36
00:03:25.501 --> 00:03:27.042
We should get a cat.

37
00:03:27.126 --> 00:03:30.834
[Man] You can write all day. every day.
Nothing but the birds singing.

38
00:03:33.792 --> 00:03:35.501
[Grace] How did he die?

39
00:03:36.542 --> 00:03:38.334
[Man] Um...

40
00:03:39.876 --> 00:03:41.792
- I don't know.
- [Grace chuckles]

41
00:03:43.584 --> 00:03:45.751
[She climbs up the stairs]

42
00:03:56.209 --> 00:03:58.792
[She climbs down the stairs]

43
00:04:10.959 --> 00:04:12.084
Here we are.

44
00:04:15.626 --> 00:04:17.792
- We need a broom.
- [They laugh]

45
00:04:18.292 --> 00:04:20.751
[Harsh. fast-paced rock music]

46
00:05:08.334 --> 00:05:10.167
[Music continues]

47
00:05:30.792 --> 00:05:33.626
[Music halts;
Insects chirp and buzz]

48
00:05:54.667 --> 00:05:59.084
[Pinky & Perky's version of
<i>Let's Twist Again</i> plays in the distance]

49
00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:16.917
[Man] Hey. hey. hey.

50
00:06:17.001 --> 00:06:18.084
- [Baby cries]
- Hey.

51
00:06:19.376 --> 00:06:20.376
Hey.

52
00:06:20.459 --> 00:06:22.584
[He sings]? <i>Came on. let's twist again?</i>

53
00:06:25.209 --> 00:06:27.917
- Hey! Where's your mommy?
- [Crying continues]

54
00:06:28.626 --> 00:06:30.334
Pumpkin. where's your mommy?

55
00:06:32.959 --> 00:06:35.251
[Baby gurgles]

56
00:06:38.751 --> 00:06:41.001
[Man babbles in singsong]

57
00:06:43.459 --> 00:06:45.167
Oh. no!

58
00:06:58.209 --> 00:06:59.917
Where's Mommy?

59
00:07:01.459 --> 00:07:03.792
[Music continues]

60
00:07:21.376 --> 00:07:23.084
Oh. God.

61
00:07:25.751 --> 00:07:26.834
Grace.

62
00:07:50.209 --> 00:07:52.001
[Music halts]

63
00:07:52.084 --> 00:07:54.334
[Insects buzz;
Baby coos]

64
00:07:56.751 --> 00:07:57.959
Mom wanted to stop by.

65
00:08:00.959 --> 00:08:02.167
Oh?

66
00:08:02.959 --> 00:08:06.334
I told her it wasn't a big deal.
It's like a "us" thing.

67
00:08:06.417 --> 00:08:08.542
And it's just for six months.
anyway. so...

68
00:08:10.584 --> 00:08:12.376
[Grace] Mm-hmm.

69
00:08:13.292 --> 00:08:14.584
I just feel kind of bad.

70
00:08:14.667 --> 00:08:17.917
'cause I think she just wants the company.

71
00:08:18.876 --> 00:08:20.626
I don't mind her coming.

72
00:08:23.709 --> 00:08:27.417
It's weird. It's like she doesn't
know how to function any more.

73
00:08:28.251 --> 00:08:30.792
She's still cooking for two people.
Did she tell you that?

74
00:08:32.751 --> 00:08:34.376
It's too sweet.

75
00:08:35.042 --> 00:08:37.209
Yeah? No. it's nice.

76
00:08:38.792 --> 00:08:39.917
He liked it.

77
00:08:42.667 --> 00:08:44.501
A real mom would have baked a cake.

78
00:08:46.626 --> 00:08:48.459
[He scoffs]

79
00:08:51.334 --> 00:08:52.751
Want another one?

80
00:08:57.376 --> 00:08:58.876
Why is it so fuckin' hot?

81
00:09:00.792 --> 00:09:03.251
[She mimics his voice]
"Why is it so fuckin' hot?"

82
00:09:03.709 --> 00:09:05.792
"Why is it so fuckin' hot?"

83
00:09:05.876 --> 00:09:07.584
It's always hot.

84
00:09:08.376 --> 00:09:10.459
[Baby coos]

85
00:09:15.001 --> 00:09:17.251
[Record whirrs]

86
00:09:17.334 --> 00:09:19.501
[Insects chirp]

87
00:09:51.167 --> 00:09:53.417
[Baby cries]

88
00:09:57.292 --> 00:09:59.376
[Baby gurgles]

89
00:10:10.792 --> 00:10:13.167
[Baby coos]

90
00:11:22.709 --> 00:11:25.167
[Faint. unsettling buzz]

91
00:11:26.084 --> 00:11:28.501
[Insects chirp and buzz]

92
00:11:41.167 --> 00:11:42.376
Boy's asleep.

93
00:11:43.584 --> 00:11:45.417
[Man] Mm-hmm.

94
00:11:48.751 --> 00:11:50.792
[He hums]

95
00:11:54.626 --> 00:11:56.959
[He spits]

96
00:11:57.042 --> 00:11:59.167
[Motorcycle revs nearby]

97
00:12:03.626 --> 00:12:06.042
[Revving fades into the distance]

98
00:12:16.459 --> 00:12:17.876
You wanna look?

99
00:12:20.959 --> 00:12:23.251
How can you not give a shit
about the stars. Grace?

100
00:12:23.917 --> 00:12:26.667
Well. they make me feel like nothing.

101
00:12:28.501 --> 00:12:31.751
[Man] I like they make me feel like
I'm part of something bigger.

102
00:12:33.501 --> 00:12:35.001
You like to feel like nothing?

103
00:12:35.084 --> 00:12:36.167
[Man] No.

104
00:12:36.251 --> 00:12:39.042
You know how many universes
there are out there?

105
00:12:39.667 --> 00:12:42.751
What are we doing in
the different universe? Are we together?

106
00:12:42.834 --> 00:12:43.876
[Man] Sure we are.

107
00:12:45.709 --> 00:12:47.042
Am I a rock star?

108
00:12:47.667 --> 00:12:48.917
[Man] Hmm...

109
00:12:49.001 --> 00:12:51.042
Can you sing in a different universe?

110
00:12:51.626 --> 00:12:53.459
- Hey.
- [He chuckles]

111
00:12:53.542 --> 00:12:55.417
Yeah. I'm sure you're a rock star.

112
00:12:57.584 --> 00:12:58.667
Do we fuck?

113
00:12:59.667 --> 00:13:01.376
[Man] Uh-huh.

114
00:13:03.834 --> 00:13:05.042
All the time?

115
00:13:06.709 --> 00:13:07.709
Hey. what?

116
00:13:08.376 --> 00:13:10.084
Do. We. Fuck?

117
00:13:12.001 --> 00:13:13.959
Like rabbits.

118
00:13:15.334 --> 00:13:17.834
[He chuckles]

119
00:13:27.167 --> 00:13:28.417
Do you hear him?

120
00:13:29.584 --> 00:13:30.626
[Man] No.

121
00:13:33.209 --> 00:13:34.709
He's crying. Listen.

122
00:13:36.417 --> 00:13:38.126
[Man] Grace. it's totally silent.

123
00:13:44.209 --> 00:13:45.334
Am I boring you?

124
00:13:45.876 --> 00:13:47.716
- [Grace] Not you. The universe.
- [Door opens]

125
00:13:47.792 --> 00:13:50.209
- Who gives a shit?
- [Door closes]

126
00:13:55.917 --> 00:13:57.417
[He sighs]

127
00:13:57.501 --> 00:13:59.060
[TV presenter]...<i>and a wild party mom...</i>

128
00:13:59.084 --> 00:14:02.792
[Woman on TV]<i>I'm very well known as
Big Bouncy. the over-the-hill party girl.</i>

129
00:14:02.876 --> 00:14:05.376
[TV presenter]...<i>swap lives
for two weeks.</i>

130
00:14:06.126 --> 00:14:09.001
- [Woman 2 on TV] <i>I hope you survive.</i>
- [Boy on TV] <i>Bye!</i>

131
00:14:09.084 --> 00:14:11.792
- [Woman] <i>Nice to meet you.</i>
- [Soft rattling]

132
00:14:13.251 --> 00:14:15.667
<i>We are two worlds apart.</i>

133
00:14:15.751 --> 00:14:18.417
[Woman 2]<i>I've never seen
anything good come out of alcohol.</i>

134
00:14:18.501 --> 00:14:20.584
[Woman]<i>I've never
killed an animal before.</i>

135
00:14:20.667 --> 00:14:22.667
<i>Oh. my God!</i>

136
00:14:22.751 --> 00:14:24.126
[Boy] <i>I'm talking!</i>

137
00:14:24.209 --> 00:14:26.876
[Woman 2]<i>I've never seen
a more disrespectful child.</i>

138
00:14:28.084 --> 00:14:30.167
[Soft rattling]

139
00:14:34.501 --> 00:14:36.542
[Soft rattling]

140
00:14:39.626 --> 00:14:41.709
[Horse whinnies in the distance]

141
00:14:53.751 --> 00:14:56.042
[Horse neighs]

142
00:15:02.084 --> 00:15:04.376
[Horse neighs intensely]

143
00:15:19.209 --> 00:15:21.292
[Soft snoring]

144
00:15:27.209 --> 00:15:29.334
[He grunts sleepily]

145
00:15:51.251 --> 00:15:53.126
[She sighs]

146
00:16:01.584 --> 00:16:03.292
[Woman] <i>Does it feel like a girl?</i>

147
00:16:04.542 --> 00:16:06.667
[Grace] <i>What does a girl feel like?</i>

148
00:16:06.751 --> 00:16:10.376
[Woman]<i>If it moves more on the right.
then you're probably having a boy.</i>

149
00:16:11.709 --> 00:16:13.126
<i>You didn't wanna know?</i>

150
00:16:14.709 --> 00:16:16.584
[Grace] <i>Mm-mm.</i>

151
00:16:16.667 --> 00:16:19.459
Grace. I...

152
00:16:19.542 --> 00:16:22.376
I didn't find out
what I was having either.

153
00:16:22.459 --> 00:16:23.667
I think that's nice.

154
00:16:23.751 --> 00:16:25.959
You didn't find out
'cause you wanted a girl.

155
00:16:26.042 --> 00:16:27.709
[She laughs ironically] Ha. ha.

156
00:16:27.792 --> 00:16:30.001
Oh. gosh. He forgets to drink.

157
00:16:30.084 --> 00:16:32.667
- Harry. you gotta have a drink.
- [Woman 3] He's fine.

158
00:16:32.751 --> 00:16:35.459
No. I didn't. I wanted a baby.
I wanted whoever was in there.

159
00:16:35.542 --> 00:16:37.209
Yeah? And you got Jackson?

160
00:16:37.292 --> 00:16:38.667
Unlucky.

161
00:16:38.751 --> 00:16:40.167
I heard that. Auntie Jen.

162
00:16:40.251 --> 00:16:42.917
[Sports reporter speaks indistinctly]

163
00:16:43.001 --> 00:16:44.459
Are you off your food. Grace?

164
00:16:45.876 --> 00:16:47.834
- Leave her alone.
- You didn't eat.

165
00:16:47.917 --> 00:16:50.501
Being pregnant makes your stomach shrink.

166
00:16:51.292 --> 00:16:52.376
[Woman] That's bullshit.

167
00:16:52.459 --> 00:16:54.667
[Jen] It's sucking on you
every minute of the day.

168
00:16:54.751 --> 00:16:57.167
Then you'll be famished.
I couldn't get enough in me.

169
00:16:57.251 --> 00:16:58.917
[Woman] That never went away. did it?

170
00:16:59.001 --> 00:17:01.376
- [Women laugh]
- You can talk. What's your excuse?

171
00:17:01.459 --> 00:17:04.626
[Jen] Never had a baby but always
ate as though you'd just had triplets.

172
00:17:04.709 --> 00:17:06.709
[Women laugh]

173
00:17:06.792 --> 00:17:09.042
You know. Grace.
if you get a screamer...

174
00:17:09.126 --> 00:17:11.001
[Woman 2] She's not gonna get a screamer.

175
00:17:11.084 --> 00:17:12.667
[Woman] Jackson was a screamer.

176
00:17:12.751 --> 00:17:15.542
- [Jackson] That's a lie!
- [Woman 2] Jackson was a sweetheart.

177
00:17:15.626 --> 00:17:18.667
The point is. if you do.
let the baby cry.

178
00:17:18.751 --> 00:17:22.042
Just walk away from it.
Don't let yourself get tired. stressed.

179
00:17:22.126 --> 00:17:24.042
[Woman 2] That's a horrible thing to say.

180
00:17:24.126 --> 00:17:25.792
[Jen] Slow fuckin' death.

181
00:17:25.876 --> 00:17:29.417
If you're not at your best. it's no good
for anyone. especially the baby.

182
00:17:29.501 --> 00:17:32.042
[Woman] And a crying baby
doesn't mean it's in pain.

183
00:17:32.126 --> 00:17:34.792
[Jen] It's the only way they have
of communicating.

184
00:17:34.876 --> 00:17:35.876
[Woman 2] No. it's not.

185
00:17:35.959 --> 00:17:39.501
People say that shit because
they wanna walk away from their kid.

186
00:17:39.584 --> 00:17:41.584
Anyway. all I do is take care of Harry.

187
00:17:41.667 --> 00:17:43.507
- [Woman] Barely.
- [Woman 2] If you need me...

188
00:17:43.542 --> 00:17:45.917
- [Jen] She doesn't.
- [Woman 2]...we're just a walk away.

189
00:17:46.001 --> 00:17:48.959
What you doing in here. Pop?
Wanna watch the Grizzlies?

190
00:17:50.626 --> 00:17:52.376
Wanna open some of those presents?

191
00:17:52.876 --> 00:17:54.626
Whose presents?

192
00:17:54.709 --> 00:17:56.084
For the baby.

193
00:17:56.167 --> 00:17:59.417
No. I gotta sort out these shoes.

194
00:17:59.501 --> 00:18:02.167
- Okay.
- They're the wrong ones.

195
00:18:03.501 --> 00:18:05.209
They look good to me.

196
00:18:05.292 --> 00:18:08.792
- You had enough to eat. Mom?
- Honey. I'm stuffed.

197
00:18:08.876 --> 00:18:11.334
Would you get your dad
something to drink. please?

198
00:18:11.417 --> 00:18:12.959
Here you go. Pop.

199
00:18:14.042 --> 00:18:15.751
No more pie.

200
00:18:18.334 --> 00:18:20.042
[Woman 2] Well. I'm stuffed.

201
00:18:21.251 --> 00:18:23.667
[Jen] Can't stop eating.
It's the same every holiday.

202
00:18:23.751 --> 00:18:25.834
Well. you can do it.
You've always been skinny.

203
00:18:25.917 --> 00:18:27.584
Grace likes me lean.
Don't you. baby?

204
00:18:27.667 --> 00:18:29.334
You can starve in January.

205
00:18:29.417 --> 00:18:30.917
[Women laugh]

206
00:18:31.001 --> 00:18:34.292
What are y'all doing?
Why are y'all here?

207
00:18:34.376 --> 00:18:36.459
This is Frank's house.

208
00:18:36.542 --> 00:18:37.959
It's his house.

209
00:18:38.042 --> 00:18:40.501
Harry. this is Grace and Jackson's...

210
00:18:40.584 --> 00:18:42.876
No. this is my brother's house.

211
00:18:42.959 --> 00:18:45.376
[Woman 2] Sweetheart. Frank's not here.

212
00:18:45.459 --> 00:18:48.126
Get out of my brother's house!

213
00:18:48.209 --> 00:18:50.001
[Grace giggles]

214
00:18:52.376 --> 00:18:54.126
[She clears her throat]

215
00:18:57.292 --> 00:18:59.584
[Thuds and clattering in the distance]

216
00:19:15.959 --> 00:19:17.876
[Jackson exhales deeply]

217
00:19:18.876 --> 00:19:21.042
- Jackson.
- [Jackson groans. softly]

218
00:19:23.959 --> 00:19:26.292
[Clattering continues]

219
00:19:43.917 --> 00:19:45.001
Harry.

220
00:19:53.626 --> 00:19:55.792
[Door creaks. opens]

221
00:19:59.751 --> 00:20:01.126
Harry!

222
00:20:06.626 --> 00:20:08.626
[Insects chirp]

223
00:20:09.584 --> 00:20:11.459
Did you find the right size?

224
00:20:22.834 --> 00:20:24.251
Hello.

225
00:20:25.251 --> 00:20:26.751
Hello.

226
00:20:30.501 --> 00:20:32.417
[He gasps. emotional]

227
00:20:33.959 --> 00:20:35.917
Is it a baby?

228
00:20:36.001 --> 00:20:38.001
- A baby.
- [Harry] A boy?

229
00:20:39.001 --> 00:20:41.876
I don't know.
I think. maybe.

230
00:20:41.959 --> 00:20:43.042
[Harry] It is.

231
00:20:43.792 --> 00:20:45.042
Oh?

232
00:20:45.126 --> 00:20:47.126
Don't leave him to cry.

233
00:20:49.376 --> 00:20:50.584
I won't.

234
00:20:51.709 --> 00:20:54.001
You know. when he comes. he's a cat.

235
00:20:55.042 --> 00:20:57.501
He's a bear and a baby.

236
00:20:58.209 --> 00:21:01.001
And he's you. he's all of you.

237
00:21:01.084 --> 00:21:02.709
He's gonna be so funny.

238
00:21:02.792 --> 00:21:05.251
[They chuckle]

239
00:21:05.334 --> 00:21:08.709
[Waltz-like rhythm.
romantic French chanson]

240
00:21:27.876 --> 00:21:30.501
[Music continues]

241
00:21:38.084 --> 00:21:40.334
[He sniffles]

242
00:22:23.417 --> 00:22:25.876
[Music continues. muffled;
Insects chirp]

243
00:22:39.667 --> 00:22:41.751
[Music concludes;
Wind blows]

244
00:23:00.751 --> 00:23:03.042
[Lively music plays in store]

245
00:23:14.042 --> 00:23:16.292
Hi. Find everything you're looking for?

246
00:23:16.917 --> 00:23:18.126
[Grace] In life?

247
00:23:18.209 --> 00:23:19.376
[Clerk chuckles]

248
00:23:19.459 --> 00:23:21.167
Any gas for your car?

249
00:23:21.251 --> 00:23:23.042
- [Grace] No.
- Alrighty.

250
00:23:23.126 --> 00:23:26.751
I love this stuff. Whatever they put
in that powder. it's like magic.

251
00:23:26.834 --> 00:23:29.042
It's two for six dollars
if you want another.

252
00:23:29.126 --> 00:23:30.459
- I'm good.
- This one's four.

253
00:23:30.542 --> 00:23:32.334
- And the other one is two.
- I get it.

254
00:23:32.417 --> 00:23:34.376
- No. thanks.
- He's a boy. right?

